Brynek [ˈbrɨnɛk] (German: Brunneck) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Tworóg, within Tarnowskie Góry County, Silesian Voivodeship, in southern Poland. It lies approximately 3 kilometres (2 mi) south-east of Tworóg, 13 km (8 mi) north-west of Tarnowskie Góry, and 36 km (22 mi) north-west of the regional capital Katowice.